cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with learning a common latent space for multiple modalities, specifically in the context of image captioning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for learning from unpaired multi-modal data, which is a problem that is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with generating captions for images. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with learning from multiple modalities.
